<http://www.isid.org>
Date: Fri, 5 Sep 2003 20:59:00 +0100
From: Pablo Nart <pablo.nart@ntlworld.com>
Source: Eurosurveillance Weekly 2003 Volume 7 / Issue 36 [edited]
<http://www.eurosurveillance.org/ew/2003/030904.asp>

Outbreak of _Salmonella bareilly_ in the United Kingdom: update
---------------------------------------------------------------
The cumulative total of cases of _Salmonella bareilly_ in England and Wales
since 1 Aug 2003, confirmed by England and Wales' Health Protection Agency
Laboratory of Enteric Pathogens (LEP), has risen to 108 (1, 2). There are
also 23 cases in Scotland.
The epidemic curve is consistent with a continuing source, and the last
known date of onset is now 23 Aug 2003. Following hypothesis-generating
interviews, a national case control study began on 30 Aug 2003. Medical
microbiologists in England and Wales have been asked to ensure that Group
C1 Salmonellas (O6,7:y:1,5) are referred for confirmation and typing as
quickly as possible.
Dr Sarah O'Brien (telephone +44 20 8200 6868 extension 4422) or Dr Bob Adak
(extension 4551) at the Health Protection Agency's Communicable Disease
Surveillance Center would be grateful to hear of any suspected cases of _S.
bareilly_ that might be linked to the outbreak in the United Kingdom.
References:
1. Health Protection Agency. National increase in Salmonella Bareilly -
update. Commun Dis Rep CDR Wkly 2003; 13 (36): news.
<http://www.phls.co.uk/publications/cdr/index.html>
2. O'Brien S, Ward L, Hampton M, Cowden J, Mather H, Brown D. Increase in
Salmonella Bareilly in the United Kingdom. Eurosurveillance Weekly 2003; 7
(35): 28/08/2003. <http://www.eurosurveillance.org/ew/2003/030828.asp>
[Byline: Sarah O'Brien, John Cowden, John Coia, and Linda Ward Health
Protection Agency Communicable Disease Surveillance Centre, Health
Protection Agency Laboratory of Enteric Pathogens, London, England; and
Scottish Centre for Infection and Environmental Health Scottish Salmonella
Reference Laboratory, Glasgow, Scotland]
